article.help
  .container-fluid
    section.row-fluid.summary
      .summary.col-sm-3
        h3 Help
        p.lead What is all this?
      .details.col-sm-9
        p
          | The Tengu Open Source UI is based on the Neo4j Browser.
          | It uses the same mechanism as the Neo4j Browser: the command shell. 
          | Use the editor bar up above &uarr; to enter client-side commands. 
          | Each command will produce a "frame" like this one in the result stream.
        p Use the&nbsp;
          code :help
          | command to learn about other topics.
        p
          | New to Tengu? Try one of the guides to learn the basics.

        table.table-condensed.table-help
          tr
            th Usage:
            td
              code :help &lt;topic&gt;
          tr
            th Topics:
            td
              a(help-topic="commands") :help commands
          tr
            th Guides:
            td
              a(play-topic="tengu") :play tengu
          tr
            th Example models:
            td
              a(tengu-model="storm") :tengu model create storm
              br
              a(tengu-model="spark") :tengu model create spark
              br
              a(play-topic="cityot") :tengu model create cityot
          tr
            th Reference:
            td
              a(href="http://www.tengu.io") Tengu Product website
              br
              a(href="http://tengu.intec.ugent.be") Tengu Academic website


